<p>
<br><br><strong>Sister: </strong>So, you are telling me that you could do a better job as President than all of those hopefuls out there that have dedicated their life to their country?

<br><br><strong>Brother: </strong>Yes, it would be quite easy.

<br><br><strong>Sister: </strong>O.k. I'll bite, what is your plan?

<br><br><strong>Brother: </strong>I would be the first AI president.

<br><br><strong>Sister: </strong>The first AI president? O.k. I am intrigued. Give me your introductory speech.

<br><br><strong>Brother: </strong>It would go something like this:
"Hello my fellow Americans, my name is John Q. Hopeful, and I want to be your first AI president.

First, I want to acknowledgie that AI can be used for bad intentions. Bad people can use it to do bad things.... and if elected president, I can assure you that I will use the powers of the government to protect the people as best I can.""

<br><br><strong>Sister: </strong>And exactly how are you going to protect the people.

<br><br><strong>Brother: </strong>There are lot's of ways. For instance, online and phone scams are pretty common in our lives these days. We can use AI to track those scams down faster, saving a lot of people a lot of time and money...... but we are getting off track, can I finish my speech?

<br><br><strong>Sister: </strong>Why of course, please continue Mr. Presidential hopeful.

<br><br><strong>Brother: </strong>So after acknowledging the dangers I would go right in to explaing how we can use it to our benefit. I would say something like:
 "Having said that, AI gives us the ability to transform our society in a transcendental way.

<br><br>Let me first explain AI in a simple way that most people can understand. Basically, you can ask AI questions and it takes all of the data it has collected and sorts through that data in a "supposedly" non-partisian manner to give you the best answer.

<br><br><strong>Sister: </strong>Why did you put up "bunny ears" when you said supposedly?

<br><br><strong>Brother: </strong>Because it is difficult to know for sure that a particular AI company does not have a "partisian bend". I would like to see the government get involved in regulating the AI industry, but that is a topic for another day.
... continuing with my speech "If you want a more detailed description of what AI is all about, you can simply ask something like below:"

