I read that they are trying to break up Salt Lake City into 4 different districts. On the common sense meter, that rates a 0. Unless, of course, they are going to do that to all large cities.

For the current events board, the idea is to get a good pulse on what the U.S. citizens think on a certain subject. If we have this limited to U.S. citizens it would help us work through the clutter that is created by people outside of the country trying to affect our opinions.

